CRICKET - AUSTRALIA POISED FOR THIRD TEST VICTORY . Australia were heading for victory in the third test after reducing England to 130 for five on Sunday as they chased a massive 469 to win . England lost their first four wickets in the second innings in a spell of 37 balls either side of tea . Only John Crawley , playing for his place after a poor run , resisted , with an unbeaten 53 . Australia declared their second innings at 395 for eight , Steve Waugh becoming the first batsman for 50 years to make two centuries in an Ashes encounter . Not even the English weather , which has been poor in recent weeks , is likely to deny Australia a victory to level the six - match series at 1 - 1 . The forecast for Monday ' s final day is " dry and warm " . 
